      transform, analyze, transmit, and otherwise use Clinic Data only as reasonably necessary
      to provide, secure, maintain, troubleshoot, support, improve, and develop DigiHoof and
      related services, and as otherwise described in these Terms and our Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Internal Review, Research, and Product Improvement</h2>
    <p>
      DigiHoof may evaluate uploaded images, associated metadata, annotations, reports,
      workflow events, support communications, and clinic interactions for internal purposes
      such as troubleshooting, customer support, quality assurance, security, model evaluation,
      measurement validation, product development, internal research, and improving clinical
      workflow features. We do not sell Clinic Data. We do not publish, distribute, or disclose
      identifiable studies to the public, other clinics, marketing audiences, or unrelated third
      parties without your permission, except where required by law, necessary to protect the
      service, or necessary for trusted service providers acting on our behalf under
      confidentiality or data-protection obligations. Where reasonably practical for internal
      research and improvement, DigiHoof will use de-identified, pseudonymized, aggregated, or
      minimized data rather than directly identifiable clinic or client data.
    </p>

    <h2>6. User Responsibilities and Permissions</h2>
    <p>
      You are responsible for ensuring that you have all rights, permissions, client
      authorizations, and legal authority required to upload, process, store, and share Clinic
      Data through DigiHoof. You are responsible for complying with laws, regulations,
      professional rules, record-retention obligations, and confidentiality duties that apply to
      veterinary medical records and client communications in your jurisdiction. You must not
      upload human medical images or human protected health information to DigiHoof.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Account Security</h2>
    <p>
      You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login credentials,
      controlling account access, and promptly notifying us of suspected unauthorized access.
      Actions taken through your account may be treated as authorized by you or your clinic
